{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4f482a49-8e70-42b6-b07a-e11e27667e58","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's what to watch for:\n\n**Framework support dropped:** MSTest v3 no longer supports `netcoreapp3.1` or `net5.0` — both are end-of-life. You'd need to update those targets to `net6.0` or later (ideally `net8.0`). `net462` is still supported.\n\n**Package consolidation:** In v3, replace the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages with the single **`MSTest`** metapackage.\n\n**Notable breaking changes:**\n- `[TestClass]` is now **required** on all test classes (previously optional in some scenarios).\n- Some `Assert` overloads and behaviors changed.\n- `DataRow` attribute has stricter type matching.\n- `ClassInitialize` / `ClassCleanup` inheritance behavior changed.\n\n**Minimum migration** for your project would be:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n<!-- remove MSTest.TestFramework and MSTest.TestAdapter -->\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"590f3823-e026-41f5-80d7-f86e04068b34","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me check what I know about MSTest v3 compatibility:\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x) has the following key changes:\n- It requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2 (so net462 is fine)\n- It dropped support for .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0 (these are out of support)\n- Actually, let me be more precise. MSTest v3 minimum supported TFMs are:\n  - .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n  - .NET 6.0+ (or maybe .NET 8.0+?)\n\nAlso, in MSTest v3, the package structure changed - you use a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.\n\nSo looking at the target frameworks: `net462` should work fine with MSTest v3, but `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are both out of support and won't be compatible with MSTest v3.\n\nThe main migration steps are consolidating the MSTest packages into one, dropping or updating those unsupported target frameworks to `net6.0` or `net8.0`, and dealing with various API breaking changes like `Assert` method updates and stricter `[TestClass]` attribute requirements.","outputTokens":776,"requestId":"A041:243205:1BA3BD8:1F99568:69FE9FFC"},"id":"b46870de-ed8c-4345-bef7-d3142cc0ce74","timestamp":"2026-05-09T02:46:35.779Z","parentId":"caa30725-82e9-463c-860a-d92fee1624b2"}
